Package: yaamake
Architecture: all
Depends:
 yaamake-makefiles,
 ${misc:Depends},
Suggests:
 git,
Description: Makefile system to build and program AVR projects
 Yaamake is handy makefile system to be used with gnu make
 for building and programming AVR projects. IT allows you to
 write simple Makefile with few variable definitions and
 upplies lot of defined targets (actions).
 .
 Yaamake is mainly used by Yaal project, but it's also
 very useful separately.
 .
 This package contains tool to find location of actual makefiles.

Package: yaamake-serialconsole
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
Enhances:
 yaamake-makefiles1,
Section: comm
Description: Simple serial communication utility
 Very simple shell tool using common linux utilities for
 communicating with serial device like AVR microcontroller.
 .
 This software is designed to be trivial implementation of
 serial communication program for yaamake-makefiles.
 .
 For better program, try minicom, tinyserial, picocom or similar.

